Grateful to have been blessed with so much in this life, the opportunity of giving back to my people and so grateful for my incredible friends for sharing their love and generosity to help families in need in my beloved country. Thank you @menieurluis for always inspiring me and for opening the doors to this beautiful cause alongside @fundacionfelixmdiaz which is a non-profit that is working to help, inspire and uplift the youth and the community in Dominican Rep. 

Thanks to my fellow Friends, colleagues who are a big part of this few days @rafaelmieses_ @manuelasancheztsh @kleydhermartinez our goal is to continue building so we can do projects like this one more often.  Thank you all for your love and support ❤️

El pasado 6 de enero día de los reyes magos, colaboré junto a la fundación @fundacionfelixmdiaz @menieurluis para traer sonrisas a los niños de mi país. Como ustedes saben algunos sectores de la cuidad Santo Domingo donde las posibilidades son muy precarias es muy importante poder ayudar a nuestra juventud.
Especialmente en esta temporada de celebración es muy importante ver esas caritas felices lo cual no tiene precio. Gracias por estar para nuestros niños e inspirarme para ser parte de este día tan importante. No pude estar presente pero mi corazón y espíritu definitivamente estuvo con ustedes! 💗🏀🚲🚗🏐⚾️🏓🪁🏹🛝🥏🏈🛼🛹

While most of us celebrate the holidays at home with loved ones, it can be easy to forget how lucky we are. Many children aren’t so fortunate, spending their holidays in the hospital. This year, we made it a priority to show them they are not forgotten. At the Hugo Mendoza pediatric hospital we were able to bring a little magic and cheer to the children who couldn’t be home for the holidays. I feel so blessed to have been one of many helping hands in this process, and I’ll never forget the smiles and joy we brought to those who needed them most. @menieurluis @rafaelmieses_ @kleydhermartinez 🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾

I stand with the women and the people of Iran today and all days. I am a Dominican woman trying my best every day to advocate for what I believe in and encourage others to be themselves. So, I stand here today in solidarity with the Iranian people and encourage everyone to help in any way they feel called. I love you, the people of Iran and I stand with you. WOMAN, LIFE, FREEDOM.

Mi querido Montecristi! El pueblo que me vio nacer! Una tierra llena de gente buena, trabajadora y muy feliz. Poseemos de arduos profesionales en todas las industrias. 

Pueblo mío de donde salí a representar mi país en la moda, junto a Luis Menieur diseñador Montecristeño y scout de modelos. Grandes deportistas como Osbaldo Virgil (Ozzie), Juan Marichal, Toni Peña, Artistas como Fernando Villallalona, Raulin Rodríguez, Luis vargas, Antonny Santos, Cardi B, y muchos mas! 

Que decir de sus aguas azules del Atlántico. 
El Morro Parque Nacional, guardián de nuestro pueblo, donde habitan bellas especies, Manglares que son un sueño, y sus 7 cayos que reciben muchos, llenando de alegría a cada persona que visita. 

Yo soy montecristeña con mucho orgullo! Mi gente linda tenemos mucho y aquel que no lo ha visitado o leído de ella que estudie y deje de ser tan ignorante. 🌊🏝️

#montecristi #cayoarena #elmorromontecristi #plataformadelmorro #visitamontecristi #orgullosadesermontecristeña

Incredibly proud of my sister @austriaulloa @404artcollection on her curated exhibition. 
The Revealer by Frédéric Bruly Bouabré. Few days left to come and see the exhibition in Miami at @artlife gallery until December 10th.

Frédéric Bruly Bouabré (1923–2014) was a Ivorian artist and poet, renowned for his significant contributions to contemporary African art. 
A visionary who developed a unique script system consisting of over 400 syllabic characters, known as “Bété syllabary,” aimed at preserving and promoting African languages. 
His intricate drawings, often accompanied by poetic narratives, served as a visual representation of his cultural heritage.
Bouabré’s work gained international recognition, with exhibitions in major art institutions worldwide, including the Venice Biennale, The Centre Pompidou, The Dia Foundation, The Tate Modern and The Museum of Modern Art in NYC, 
His creations blend traditional African aesthetics with a modern, symbolic language, reflecting a profound commitment to preserving and celebrating the rich cultural diversity of the African continent.
